        "timestamp": 1703184503
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And indeed Yaël is right to point out that <code>i</code> is used twice independently, because the one in <code>⋂ i, A i</code> is bound by the intersection symbol and does not interact with the outer one.</p>",
